<c74object name='dk.datadelay' category='' module='dataknot'>
    <digest>Delays incoming descriptor data like a lossy &#39;analog&#39; delay
</digest>
    <description>The <o>dk.datadelay</o> object takes incoming descriptors (of any kind) and sends them through a delay line. The feedback and rolloff parameters function as they would in a conventional delay. The input can be lists or <o>buffer~</o> s and the same will be output.
</description>
    <discussion>Since this is a somewhat abstract idea, I&#39;ve done my best to apply what is perceptually meaningful (where possible) changes to the material as it is delayed and decayed. This is different for each descriptor type, and is more effective in some than others. On the normal descriptors (i.e. <o>dk.descriptors~</o>) and melbands the results are perceptual and quite effective. With MFCCs, given their abstract nature, this is less the case.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, FluCoMa Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

    <!-- INLETS -->
    <inletlist>
        <inlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor and control in
</digest>
            <description>Incoming descriptors as a list or <o>buffer~</o> as well as control input.
</description>
        </inlet>
    </inletlist>
    <!-- INLETS -->

    <!-- OUTLETS -->
    <outletlist>
        <outlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor output
</digest>
            <description>Transformed descriptor output.
</description>
        </outlet>
    </outletlist>
    <!-- OUTLETS -->

    <!-- ARGUMENTS -->
    <objarglist>
    </objarglist>
    <!-- ARGUMENTS -->

    <!--MESSAGES-->
    <methodlist>
    <method name='clear'>
        <arglist>
        </arglist>
        <digest>Clear the delay line
</digest>
        <description>Clear the delay line.
</description>
    </method>
	</methodlist>
	<!--MESSAGES-->

	<!--ATTRIBUTES-->
	<attributelist>
        <attribute
        name='delay'
        type='float'
        size='1'
        get='1' set='1'
        >
        <digest>Delay time
</digest>
        <description>Delay time in <strong>ms</strong>.
</description>

        <attributelist>
            <attribute
            name='default'
            type='float'
            size='1'
            value='130'
            get='1' set='1'
            />
        </attributelist>
        </attribute>
        <attribute
        name='feedback'
        type='float'
        size='1'
        get='1' set='1'
        >
        <digest>Feedback amount
</digest>
        <description>Amount of feedback in the delay line in <strong>%</strong>.
</description>

        <attributelist>
            <attribute
            name='default'
            type='float'
            size='1'
            value='50'
            get='1' set='1'
            />
        </attributelist>
        </attribute>
        <attribute
        name='rolloff'
        type='float'
        size='1'
        get='1' set='1'
        >
        <digest>Amount of &#39;highs&#39; to rolloff
</digest>
        <description>Amount of &#39;highs&#39; to rolloff on input and in feedback path, in <strong>%</strong>.
</description>

        <attributelist>
            <attribute
            name='default'
            type='float'
            size='1'
            value='80'
            get='1' set='1'
            />
        </attributelist>
        </attribute>
        <attribute
        name='threshold'
        type='float'
        size='1'
        get='1' set='1'
        >
        <digest>Threshold for material to be not sent back into delay line
</digest>
        <description>Threshold for material to be not sent back into the feedback loop in <strong>dB</strong>.
</description>

        <attributelist>
            <attribute
            name='default'
            type='float'
            size='1'
            value='-70'
            get='1' set='1'
            />
        </attributelist>
        </attribute>
	</attributelist>
	<!--ATTRIBUTES-->

